child.description: Name of product offering price entity in enterprice product catalog (it is a data replicate; stays untouched even if the value is changed in the master application).

child.name: version
child.description: Version of product offering price entity in enterprise product catalog.

child.name: priceType
child.description: Used to indicate price. Values: 'recurringFee', 'discount', 'penalty'

child.name: recurringChargePeriod
child.description: Charge period. Values: 'min', 'hour', 'day', 'week', 'month', 'quartal', 'year'

child.name: recurringChargeDuration
child.description: 1 means every recurringChargePeriod, 2 means every second recurringChargePeriod, etc.

child.name: recurringChargeOccurrence
child.description: Number of occurrences. -1 means unlimited, 1 means onetime, 2 means twice, etc.

child.name: startDateTime
child.description: Start of charge

child.name: endDateTime
child.description: End of charge. Makes only sense in case of unlimited occurence.

child.name: currencyCode
child.description: String used as a code for specifying the currency associated to the given amounts. The ISO4217 norm uses 3 letters to define the currency (for example USD for US dollar or EUR for Euro).

child.name: taxIncludedAmount
child.description: Amount with tax.

child.name: dutyFreeAmount
child.description: Amount without tax.

child.name: taxRate
child.description: percentage value, e.g. 20
